						            [Reserved]</p>
				        </li>
				        <li class="- topic/li ">
					          <p id="d1184e35" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(c)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
						            The contracting officer shall insert the clause at <xref href="FAR-i1057393.dita#i1057393"
                        base="i1057393"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">52.219-6</xref>, Notice of Total Small Business Set-Aside, in solicitations and contracts involving total small business set-asides or reserves. This includes multiple-award contracts when orders may be set aside for any of the small business concerns identified in <xref href="FAR-i1101771.dita#i1101771"
                        base="i1101771"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">19.000</xref>(a)(3), as described in <xref href="FAR-i1117805.dita#i1117805"
                        base="i1117805"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">8.405-5</xref> and <xref href="FAR-i1104008.dita#i1104008"
                        base="i1104008"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">16.505</xref>(b)(2)(i)(F). The clause at <xref href="FAR-i1057393.dita#i1057393"
                        base="i1057393"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">52.219-6</xref> with its Alternate I will be used when the acquisition is for a product in a class for which the Small Business Administration has waived the nonmanufacturer rule (see <xref href="FAR-i1101844.dita#i1101844"
                        base="i1101844"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">19.102</xref>(f)(4) and (5)). Use the clause at <xref href="FAR-i1057393.dita#i1057393"
                        base="i1057393"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">52.219-6</xref> with its Alternate II when including FPI in the competition in accordance with <xref href="FAR-i1100890.dita#i1100890"
                        base="i1100890"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">19.504</xref>.</p>
				        </li>
				        <li class="- topic/li ">
					          <p id="d1184e69" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(d)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
						            The contracting officer shall insert the clause at <xref href="FAR-i1057419.dita#i1057419"
                        base="i1057419"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">52.219-7</xref>, Notice of Partial Small Business Set-Aside, in solicitations and contracts involving partial small business set-asides. This includes part or parts of multiple-award contracts, including those described in <xref href="FAR-i1077300.dita#i1077300"
                        base="i1077300"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">38.101</xref>. The clause at <xref href="FAR-i1057419.dita#i1057419"
                        base="i1057419"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">52.219-7</xref> with its Alternate I will be used when the acquisition is for a product in a class for which the Small Business Administration has waived the nonmanufacturer rule (see <xref href="FAR-i1101844.dita#i1101844"
                        base="i1101844"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">19.102</xref>(f)(4) and (5)). Use the clause at <xref href="FAR-i1057419.dita#i1057419"
                        base="i1057419"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">52.219-7</xref> with its Alternate II when including FPI in the competition in accordance with <xref href="FAR-i1100890.dita#i1100890"
                        base="i1100890"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">19.504</xref>.</p>
				        </li>
				        <li class="- topic/li ">
					          <p id="d1184e97" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(e)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
						            The contracting officer shall insert the clause at <xref href="FAR-i1057730.dita#i1057730"
                        base="i1057730"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">52.219-14</xref>, Limitations on Subcontracting, in solicitations and contracts for supplies, services, and construction, if any portion of the requirement is to be set aside or reserved for small business and the contract amount is expected to exceed $150,000. This includes multiple-award contracts when orders may be set aside for small business concerns, as described in <xref href="FAR-i1117805.dita#i1117805"
                        base="i1117805"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">8.405-5</xref> and <xref href="FAR-i1104008.dita#i1104008"
                        base="i1104008"
